d reddening law and use the colors of elliptical galaxies to measure the reddening per unit Ñux density of 100 km emission. We Ðnd consistent calibration using the B[R color distribution of a sample of the 106 brightest cluster ellipticals, as well as a sample of 384 ellipticals with B[V and Mg line strength measurements. For the latter sample, we use the correlation of intrinsic B[V versus index to tighten the power of the test greatly. We demonstrate that the new maps are Mg 2 twice as accurate as the older Burstein-Heiles reddening estimates in regions of low and moderate reddening. The maps are expected to be signiÐcantly more accurate in regions of high reddening. These dust maps will also be useful for estimating millimeter emission that contaminates cosmic microwave background radiation experiments and for estimating soft X-ray absorption. We describe how to access our maps readily for general use. Subject headings : cosmic microwave background È di †use radiation È dust, extinction È infrared : ISM : continuum È interplanetary medium},
